    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chana-masala-inspired-bean-bowl-with-cultured-coconut-and-naan/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> to the pan and cook for 5-6 min or until golden and softening</p><p>Tip: Add a splash of cold water to prevent burning!</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chana-masala-inspired-bean-bowl-with-cultured-coconut-and-naan/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> and shake off any excess water</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chana-masala-inspired-bean-bowl-with-cultured-coconut-and-naan/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion is golden and softening, add your <strong>tamarind & coconut curry paste</strong> with your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, then give everything a good mix up and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chana-masala-inspired-bean-bowl-with-cultured-coconut-and-naan/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>chickpeas</strong> (no need to drain!) with all the<strong> bean water</strong> to the pan</p><p>Add your <strong>5 bean medley</strong> and give everything a good mix up until the beans are well coated</p><p>Add 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span><span class=\"text-purple\"> </span><strong>boiled water</strong>, stir everything together and cook over a medium heat for 5-6 min or until the sauce has thickened</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chana-masala-inspired-bean-bowl-with-cultured-coconut-and-naan/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the sauce has thickened, add your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> with <strong>half</strong> your <strong>cultured coconut</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) and a generous pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and stir together</p><p>Add the <strong>spinach</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until wilted \u2013 this is your <strong>chana masala-inspired bean bowl</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chana-masala-inspired-bean-bowl-with-cultured-coconut-and-naan/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>garlic & coriander naan[s]</strong> to a <strong>toaster</strong> for 1-2 min or until warmed through</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chana-masala-inspired-bean-bowl-with-cultured-coconut-and-naan/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>chana masala-inspired bean bowl</strong> topped with the <strong>remaining cultured coconut</strong> and your <strong>crispy onions</strong> with the <strong>toasted naan</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
